In antwoort aenden ue van 18 deser ick hebbe heden vernegotieert
den wisselbrief van ƒ 698:3 court gelt die ue my seynt tot
last francois poulnicq tot Cortryck te betaelen binnen gent
by de weduwe de buck & ue by provisie voor ditto somme geere

hebbe over eenige dagen voor mons zegers 1ost van de ƒ10o

ue can dinst doen maer mits hier present weynige goederen

veel sortiment vinden tgene hope niet open waeter beseren

London Wall & Will Kent
21 feb
sence my last of 17 cur recd yours of p ditto I hope the pack of cloth N2
& one of baeyes shall be shipt in time with this convoy for Rott which
by this time ought to be yett att hull for the waters in holland are not
gett open & shall be well if you can add the kersies I writt of by my
last, yett 3 ƒ aps dearer will not do, if you have non, buy non, butt
if you have anney readdy att hull or there aboard or in holland lett mee
have them provided you be so lind to leave them att formar prise
bett 3 a 4 clothes be bought & added to the formar parties according
to the inclosed patt as here under I wish all might come serney &
safe over butt the privatoos of duynquerque hae baken from
margett road severall vessels designed, for ostend that une there from
terland with butter, so our vessels from london ought to have
good convoy if I have butt amy assortiment for springh shall
dilaye ordering of more goods till all short bee pleatie again
& endeavour in the somer to morder so much that I cau be supplyes
next hold winter therefore pray buy what is well & for alove
all tread beare & shapry Ellokes, which I exspect you shall perfrime
whilst I rest
these a patt are much the same rather to N1 then 2, rather
some what lighter then as darck close mixt & well dressed if thread
tare not to be bough
